      "content": "The French Revolution, beginning in 1789 with the convening of the Estates-General on May 5th, was a period of profound social and political upheaval. The National Assembly, formed by the Third Estate on June 17th, was instrumental in drafting the Declaration of the Rights of Man and of the Citizen on August 26th, 1789. The revolution saw the storming of the Bastille on July 14th, 1789, symbolizing the uprising against tyranny. The Reign of Terror, led by the Committee of Public Safety, saw Maximilien Robespierre and Louis Antoine de Saint-Just as key figures, with the execution of King Louis XVI on January 21st, 1793, and Queen Marie Antoinette on October 16th, 1793. The Jacobins, led by Robespierre, and the Girondins, led by Jacques Brissot, were major factions during this period. The revolution culminated in 1799 with the rise of Napoleon Bonaparte, who established the Consulate on November 9th, 1799, and later declared himself Emperor on December 2nd, 1804, marking the end of the revolutionary period.",
